cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning and machine learning techniques for learning to avoid dangerous behaviors in partially observable environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of density estimates and state occupancy measures, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
